<paragraph id="8BD436C28716AA0946A0F994DF00ADCE" blockId="13.[189,1399,1638,2028]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
This species was described based on an undetermined number of specimens of both sexes collected by J. Ogilvie at 
<collectingCountry id="F37C76528716AA094729F97CDAC7AC8D" box="[308,423,1678,1704]" name="Barbados" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Barbados</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B338716AA0947B2F97CD913AC8C" author="Cockerell" box="[431,627,1678,1705]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="142" refId="ref20306" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1939. Bees of the genus Centris from Barbados, B. W. I. The Entomologist 72: 142." type="journal article" year="1939">Cockerell (1939)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type of the species was a male.A male specimen belonging to the type series is currently housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078716AA09452DF945D8FFACF4" box="[816,927,1719,1745]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
and was labeled as type by Cockerell himself. Another male of the type series was found at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078716AA094521F912D8F6ACDF" box="[828,918,1760,1786]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and was labeled by Cockerell as cotype. The female specimen mentioned in the original description was not found. The male 
<typeStatus id="54D088608716AA0942A9F8F5DE7BAD04" box="[1204,1307,1799,1825]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078716AA0946C7F8C2DA29AD6F" box="[218,329,1840,1866]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
has the following data label: [circular label with red-rimmed margin] Type [printed]\ B.M. TYPE Hym. [printed] 17B.928 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D418716AA0944C0F8AADF6AAD57" authority="Ckll." authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1939" box="[733,1034,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbadensis">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD08716AA0944C0F8AAD8A9AD57" box="[733,969,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Centris barbadensis</emphasis>
Ckll.
</taxonomicName>
Type [handwritten]\ 
<collectingCountry id="F37C76528716AA09431DF8AADE13AD57" box="[1280,1395,1880,1906]" name="Barbados" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Barbados</collectingCountry>
. 27.4.38. (J. Ogilvie) [handwritten]\ Type in Banks Coll. [printed]. The male 
<typeStatus id="54D088608716AA094227F873DFFFADBE" box="[1082,1183,1921,1947]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">paratype</typeStatus>
housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078716AA094300F873DE17ADBE" box="[1309,1399,1921,1947]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry id="F37C76528716AA094407F85AD9EDADE7" box="[538,653,1960,1986]" name="Barbados" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Barbados</collectingCountry>
. 27.4.38. (J. Ogilvie) [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D418716AA094259F85BDE16ADE6" authority="Ckll." authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1939" box="[1092,1398,1960,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbadensis">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD08716AA094259F85BDE53ADE7" box="[1092,1331,1960,1987]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Centris barbadensis</emphasis>
Ckll.
</taxonomicName>
cotype [handwritten]\ 
<typeStatus id="54D088608716AA0947DFF823D949ADCE" box="[450,553,2001,2027]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Paratype</typeStatus>
[printed] 54874 [handwritten] USNM [printed].
</paragraph>
